29:39.774 --> 29:41.041
until they're older,

29:41.075 --> 29:44.111
past middle age, maybe
a little beaten down by life.

29:44.145 --> 29:46.113
But we want to tell you
about what your dad was like

29:46.147 --> 29:47.347
when he was young.

29:47.382 --> 29:48.749
When he could dance
like Fred Astaire.

29:48.783 --> 29:50.717
MARLEY:
And sing like Michael Bublé.

29:50.752 --> 29:51.885
He was an amazing teacher.

29:51.919 --> 29:53.420
Your dad and I almost hooked up,

29:53.454 --> 29:54.888
which means
I could have been your mom.

29:54.922 --> 29:56.962
Hit me up when you want
your first tattoo.

29:56.991 --> 29:58.358
I know a guy.

29:58.393 --> 29:59.459
If it wasn't for your dad,

29:59.494 --> 30:00.794
I would've never been
Prom Queen,

30:00.828 --> 30:02.669
though that was kind of
a bad experience for me

30:02.697 --> 30:04.131
when I think about it.

30:04.165 --> 30:06.605
But I still would've been living
my life with a fake stutter.

30:07.135 --> 30:08.435
You had to be there.

30:08.469 --> 30:10.037
Okay, it may seem
a little weird to you,

30:10.071 --> 30:11.938
but back here in the Dark Ages,

30:11.973 --> 30:14.541
it was still crazy
for girls to love girls

30:14.575 --> 30:15.876
and guys to love guys,

30:15.910 --> 30:17.711
but your dad made sure

30:17.745 --> 30:19.546
that we felt safe
loving whoever we chose.

30:19.580 --> 30:22.783
BRITTANY: He does this magic trick
where he pulls a duck out of a hat.

30:22.817 --> 30:25.919
You should have him
show you sometime.

30:25.953 --> 30:27.821
SAM: <i> Your dad had a
passion for teaching.</i>

30:27.855 --> 30:29.890
He really loved that moment
when he connected with a kid.

30:29.924 --> 30:32.059
And he was prone to
overemotional (laughs)

30:32.093 --> 30:34.094
yet often inspiring pep talks.

30:34.128 --> 30:37.164
To put it simply, I was not
a particularly nice person.

30:37.198 --> 30:39.066
(book thumps)

30:40.101 --> 30:41.735
That sweater's legit.

30:41.769 --> 30:43.070
<i>And then your dad came along,</i>

30:43.104 --> 30:44.471
and I became a man who was kind

30:44.505 --> 30:46.273
a relatively large portion
of the time.

30:46.307 --> 30:49.643
I can say without a doubt
that your dad saved my life.

30:49.677 --> 30:51.912
Little Hepburn and Tracy
wouldn't have a daddy

30:51.946 --> 30:53.313
if it wasn't for your dad.

30:53.348 --> 30:55.782
Those are the names of my kids
who aren't born yet either.

30:55.817 --> 30:56.783
We used a surrogate.

30:56.818 --> 30:58.118
I donated the egg.

30:58.152 --> 30:59.219
UNIQUE:
In the whole wide world,

30:59.253 --> 31:00.620
you'll never meet a man
more accepting

31:00.655 --> 31:03.223
and open to nature in all
its wonders than your father.

31:03.257 --> 31:04.291
He's a gem.

31:04.325 --> 31:06.460
SUE:
The best thing about your dad

31:06.494 --> 31:08.328
and that horrible perm of his

31:08.363 --> 31:12.332
is that no matter
how talentless, misshapen, ugly,

31:12.367 --> 31:15.202
miserable
or sexually ambiguous you are,

31:15.236 --> 31:17.504
he will still love you
unconditionally.

31:17.538 --> 31:20.173
