poking me in places I don't...

36:56.692 --> 37:00.261
Arthur Abrams.
(applause)

37:00.296 --> 37:02.297
(whooping, cheering)

37:07.536 --> 37:08.870
Blaine Anderson.

37:12.074 --> 37:14.175
Tina Cohen-Chang.

37:18.314 --> 37:20.849
Sam Evans.

37:23.119 --> 37:24.786
Rebecca Jackson.

37:29.859 --> 37:31.826
(whooping, cheering)

37:44.273 --> 37:47.842
Blaine, you guys, I can't
go to New York with you.

37:47.877 --> 37:50.311
Tina Cohen-Crazy. You can't
get cold feet on us now.

37:50.346 --> 37:51.780
No, it's not that.

37:51.814 --> 37:53.615
I was gonna tell you later, but

37:53.649 --> 37:56.351
the Dean of Admissions from
Brown called me this morning...

37:56.385 --> 37:59.220
And you got in? I got in.
I'm going to Brown!

37:59.255 --> 38:00.622
Oh! Tina. Congratulations.

38:00.656 --> 38:01.856
Wow, that is great.

38:01.891 --> 38:03.525
(laughing): Thank you.

38:03.559 --> 38:04.893
And, finally...

38:05.828 --> 38:07.896
Brittany S. Pierce.

38:07.930 --> 38:10.732
(cheering, applause)

38:12.802 --> 38:15.236
I called in some
favors with Sue.

38:15.271 --> 38:18.239
I figure that everybody deserves
a high school graduation,

38:18.274 --> 38:20.542
even if it's a year late.

38:20.576 --> 38:22.711
(kiss) (exclaims)

38:22.745 --> 38:26.648
You guys, I'm graduating.
(whooping)

38:29.716 --> 38:32.196
Ladies and gentlemen,
I present to you

38:32.221 --> 38:35.690
the William McKinley High
graduating class of 2013.

38:35.725 --> 38:36.925
(whooping)

38:47.003 --> 38:49.037
Brittany, I have
to tell you something.

38:49.071 --> 38:50.639
I think I've made
a huge mistake.

38:50.673 --> 38:52.774
You don't want to run away
with me, do you. What?

38:52.808 --> 38:55.510
No, no, no, no, no, no.
Of course I do.

38:55.544 --> 38:58.647
(groans) I was doing some
research on Lesbos island,

38:58.681 --> 39:01.383
and it turns out that it's not
chock-full of lesbians.

39:01.417 --> 39:03.518
It's full of German
tourists, so,

39:03.552 --> 39:05.120
I bought us our return tickets.

39:05.154 --> 39:08.189
I think that we should
go to Lesbos first,

39:08.224 --> 39:10.025
and then Hawaii
for a couple of weeks,

39:10.059 --> 39:11.059
and then come home.

39:11.093 --> 39:12.927
Well, I don't want
to go back to MIT

39:12.962 --> 39:14.596
and I can't return to Lima.

39:14.630 --> 39:18.133
I want you to come
to New York with me.

39:18.167 --> 39:20.568
Is that a yes?
Yes.

39:20.603 --> 39:22.604
(soft laugh)

39:27.276 --> 39:29.411
(sighs)

39:29.445 --> 39:31.212
Here for one last
verbal beatdown?

39:31.247 --> 39:33.515
These are my last two

39:33.549 --> 39:35.250
Razzle Dazzle Fruit
Punch wine coolers

39:35.284 --> 39:36.818
from my cellar.

39:36.852 --> 39:39.421
Company went out of
business back in the '80s,

39:39.455 --> 39:42.891
and I've been saving them
for a special occasion.

39:42.925 --> 39:45.727
Well, what could be more special
than the glee club's funeral?

39:45.761 --> 39:46.828
Mm.

39:49.365 --> 39:51.900
Well... (exhales)

39:51.934 --> 39:53.935
You finally won.

40:00.276 --> 40:03.678
Honestly, I-I don't get the
way you see the world, William,

40:03.713 --> 40:05.513
but I got to give you this:

40:05.548 --> 40:07.248
whatever it is you
did in this room,

40:07.283 --> 40:09.951
you changed a lot of kids'
lives for the better.

40:09.986 --> 40:12.520
And your own.
As you know,

40:12.555 --> 40:14.789
I find both of your
spouses intolerable

40:14.824 --> 40:18.126
and bony, but at least
this one is kind to you.

40:18.160 --> 40:19.628
Yeah, I'm not gonna miss this.

40:19.662 --> 40:22.063
Oh, I am.

40:22.098 --> 40:24.499
Nobody ever went the
distance with Sue Sylvester

40:24.533 --> 40:26.067
the way you did, Will.

40:26.102 --> 40:27.636
My whole life

40:27.670 --> 40:31.039
I've been searching for
a worthy adversary.

40:31.073 --> 40:33.041
(sighs)

40:33.075 --> 40:35.395
I'm gonna miss the fight.

40:36.879 --> 40:38.346
I could have done more.

40:38.381 --> 40:41.483
There's still so many
more kids out there.

40:41.517 --> 40:43.785
Well, who says you can't?

40:43.819 --> 40:46.187
Listen, William, you were
a horrible history teacher

40:46.222 --> 40:48.556
and you were a worse
Spanish teacher.

40:48.591 --> 40:50.692
If you're going to be
of any good to anybody,

40:50.726 --> 40:52.360
you need to be
coaching a glee club.

40:52.395 --> 40:54.329
Which is why I got
you an interview

40:54.363 --> 40:56.843
for the open slot
at Carmel High.

40:57.133 --> 40:58.533
Vocal Adrenaline?

40:58.567 --> 41:02.304
Think of what you could
accomplish with a real budget.

41:02.338 --> 41:03.538
And without somebody like me

41:03.573 --> 41:05.240
constantly trying
to take you down?

41:05.274 --> 41:06.808
Wow.

41:06.842 --> 41:08.610
I mean, tha-that's
really amazing, Sue,

41:08.644 --> 41:10.512
but they're our mortal enemies.

41:10.546 --> 41:14.416
There is no "our"
anymore, William.

41:14.450 --> 41:16.930
We're in the middle of
the new computer lab.

41:18.218 --> 41:20.698
You did what you could do here.

41:20.723 --> 41:22.624
And that was much more

41:22.658 --> 41:25.138
than I will ever care to admit.

41:26.829 --> 41:28.330
But it's really over.

41:29.932 --> 41:32.173
It's only an interview.

41:33.769 --> 41:36.010
You could always blow it.

41:44.180 --> 41:45.714
Oh, God, that's awful.

41:45.748 --> 41:48.450
Yeah, that's why they
went out of business.

41:48.484 --> 41:50.285
I'll give you a minute.

41:54.590 --> 41:56.424
(door closes)

41:58.594 --> 42:00.595
(sighs)

42:04.532 --> 42:07.612
